## SQL conventions (SQL Server 2008 R2)

The DB is on `localhost` (same machine as FastAPI). It is 14+ years old. See `.cursor/rules/30-sql-server-2008.mdc` for forbidden T-SQL features.

- Use parameterized queries always: `cursor.execute("... WHERE id = ?", (id,))`. Never f-string SQL.
- All tables in `dbo` schema, snake_case names.
- Booleans: `BIT` (0/1).
- UUIDs: `UNIQUEIDENTIFIER` with `NEWID()`.
- Timestamps: `DATETIME2(3)` for new tables; existing `DATETIME` columns stay.
- Paging: no `OFFSET/FETCH` ‚Äî use `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (...)` in a CTE.

## Auth model

- Every route except `/health`, `/auth/login` requires a valid JWT.
- JWT payload: `{sub: user_id_string, role: 'admin'|'user'|'driver', name: display_name, exp: ...}`.
- Drivers see `Pending` requests + their own `Picked Up` rows (server-side filter in queries).
- Admins see everything.
- `require_role("admin")` dependency guards admin-only routes.
- Never return `password_hash` in responses.

## Error handling

- Use `HTTPException(status_code=..., detail=...)` with clear messages.
- 401 = not logged in / token invalid. 403 = wrong role. 404 = not found.
- Don't leak DB errors to clients; log full context server-side, return generic 500.

